<TEXT>
 a russian court has rejected appeals by an american businessman who was
 arrested on spy charges in april.
 edmund pope, a businessman and former navy intelligence officer, has been
 diagnosed with a rare form of bone cancer.
 pope's lawyer wanted the court to allow a full medical examination that
 includes his own doctors.
 russian authorities say the prison doctors are adequate, and that pope is well
 enough to stand trial.
 he is accused of trying to buy secret information on a torpedo.
